# Legal-docs three-layer boundary — IDE anti-drift contract

**Canonical decision:** [ADR-0035](docs/decisions/0035-three-layer-surface-ide-anti-drift.md) (AGENTS.md **PRIORITY #2**) · Layer 1 seal: [`app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs/_SEAL.md`](../../app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs/_SEAL.md)

**If this rule and `AGENTS.md` diverge, follow `AGENTS.md` and fix this rule in the same PR.**

Public `/legal-docs/*` uses **one product name everywhere: `legal-docs`**.  
**Never** split back into `public-trust`, `legal-declarations`, or UI under `components2/marketing/`.

Mechanical guard: [`tests/unit/legal-docs-surface-contract.test.ts`](tests/unit/legal-docs-surface-contract.test.ts)  
Human seal (Layer 1): [`app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs/_SEAL.md`](app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs/_SEAL.md)

---

## Prime directive (read before any edit)

```txt
Layer 1 — app/           → URL + thin re-exports ONLY
Layer 2 — lib/features/  → routing, registry, cache, dispatch, metadata
Layer 3 — components2/   → presentation shells ONLY (no fetch, no dispatch)
```

**Import doors (only these):**

| Layer | Door |
| --- | --- |
| Layer 2 | `#features/legal-docs` · `#features/legal-docs/server` (if added) |
| Layer 3 | `#components2/legal-docs` |

---

## Layer 1 — `app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs/`

**Owns:** catch-all route file, `_SEAL.md`, `unstable_instant` re-export.

**Allowed in `page.tsx`:**

```tsx
export { unstable_instant } from "#features/legal-docs"
export {
  buildLegalDocsStaticParams as generateStaticParams,
  generateLegalDocsMetadata as generateMetadata,
  LegalDocsRoutePage as default,
} from "#features/legal-docs"
```

**Forbidden in `app/` (instant CI / review failure):**

| Action | Why |
| --- | --- |
| `resolveLegalDocsSlug`, `notFound()`, OpenStatus fetch | Layer 2 |
| `DeclarationShell`, `TrustControlSurface`, layout JSX | Layer 3 |
| `declarationDocuments`, trust fixture data | Layer 2 |
| `#components2/legal-docs` or `#components2/marketing` imports | Layer 3 — not in routes |
| Segment `dynamic` / `revalidate` / `runtime` | Cache Components policy |
| Route-level `loading.tsx` for trust/status | Use Suspense in Layer 2 |
| Recreate `public-trust` / `legal-declarations` module names | Retired |

---

## Layer 2 — `lib/features/legal-docs/`

**Owns:** declaration registry, slug routing, `generateLegalDocsMetadata`, OpenStatus cache, page orchestration (`LegalDocsRoutePage`, trust/status/declaration pages).

**Allowed module root entries only** ([`scripts/check-agent-contract.mjs`](scripts/check-agent-contract.mjs)):

```txt
actions/ · data/ · components/ · schemas/ · index.ts · server.ts · client.ts · types.ts · constants.ts · *.contract.ts · README.md
```

**Forbidden at `lib/features/legal-docs/` root:**

| Entry | Why |
| --- | --- |
| `_SEAL.md` | Not an allowed module root entry — use `app/.../legal-docs/_SEAL.md` |
| `public-trust/` · `legal-declarations/` as sibling modules | Retired — merge into `legal-docs` |
| React presentation components | Layer 3 `components2/legal-docs/` |
| Imports from `#components2/marketing` for legal-docs shells | Use `#components2/legal-docs` |

**Canonical Layer 2 files:**

| Concern | Path |
| --- | --- |
| Public barrel | `index.ts` |
| Slug + static params | `data/legal-docs-routing.shared.ts` |
| Metadata | `data/legal-docs-metadata.server.ts` |
| Declaration registry | `data/declaration-registry.shared.ts` |
| Footer links / `LEGAL_ROUTE_PREFIX` | `data/footer.shared.ts` |
| OpenStatus cache | `data/openstatus-status.server.ts` |
| Trust fixture | `data/trust-surface.fixture.shared.ts` |
| Route dispatch | `components/legal-docs-route-page.server.tsx` |
| Declaration page (`use cache`) | `components/legal-docs-declaration-page.server.tsx` |
| Trust/status pages + bodies | `components/legal-docs-trust-*.server.tsx`, `legal-docs-status-*.server.tsx` |

**Cache tiers (do not collapse):**

| Route | Strategy |
| --- | --- |
| Declarations | `LegalDocsDeclarationPage` — UI `'use cache'` + `cacheLife('max')` |
| Trust | Baseline `TrustControlSurface` Suspense fallback + cached body |
| Status | `StatusControlSkeleton` + cached body |
| Shell | `notFound()` in `LegalDocsRoutePage` **before** Suspense |

**Cross-module imports:** Other features (landing footer, sitemap, security.txt) import **`#features/legal-docs` only** — never deep paths into `data/`.

---

## Layer 3 — `components2/legal-docs/`

**Owns:** presentation-only shells for public legal/trust/status pages.

| File | Export |
| --- | --- |
| `declaration-shell.tsx` | `DeclarationShell` |
| `trust-control-surface.tsx` | `TrustControlSurface` |
| `status-control-surface.tsx` | `StatusControlSurface` |
| `status-control-skeleton.tsx` | `StatusControlSkeleton` |
| `legal-docs-status-pill.shared.tsx` | `OpenStatusPill`, `TrustSurfaceStatePill` |

**May import:** `#components2/ui/*`, `#features/legal-docs` (types, `LEGAL_ROUTE_PREFIX`, footer constants), `#i18n/navigation`, `#components2/afenda-brand`.

**Forbidden in Layer 3:**

| Action | Why |
| --- | --- |
| `getCachedOpenStatusPublicSnapshot`, `resolveLegalDocsSlug` | Layer 2 |
| `generateMetadata`, `buildLegalDocsStaticParams` | Layer 2 |
| Governed metadata renderers (`#components2/metadata`) | Bespoke marketing/legal UI only |
| Placing legal-docs UI back in `components2/marketing/` | Wrong folder — use `components2/legal-docs/` |

**Landing footer** (`components2/marketing/`) may import **`#features/legal-docs`** for link constants only — not legal-docs layout components.

---

## Retired names — do not recreate (IDE warning)

```txt
lib/features/public-trust/          ← GONE. Use lib/features/legal-docs/
lib/features/legal-declarations/    ← GONE. Use lib/features/legal-docs/
components2/marketing/declaration-shell.tsx   ← MOVED to components2/legal-docs/
components2/marketing/trust-control-surface.tsx
components2/marketing/status-control-surface.tsx
app/.../legal-declaration-page.shared.tsx       ← DELETED
```

Recreating any of the above is **forward drift** — fix imports, do not mkdir retired trees.

---

## Verification (required after every legal-docs task)

```bash
pnpm lint:path -- lib/features/legal-docs components2/legal-docs app/(main)/[locale]/legal-docs
pnpm test:fast -- tests/unit/legal-docs-surface-contract.test.ts tests/unit/public-trust-routing.test.ts tests/unit/legal-declarations-contract.test.ts
pnpm typecheck
```

`pnpm lint:agent-contract` must not report forbidden entries under `lib/features/legal-docs/`.

---

## Parity reference (same three-layer shape)

| Surface | Layer 1 `app/` | Layer 2 `lib/` | Layer 3 `components2/` |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Pre-login auth | `(auth)/` | `lib/auth/` | `components2/auth/` |
| Legal-docs | `legal-docs/` | `lib/features/legal-docs/` | `components2/legal-docs/` |
| IAM profile | `o/.../profile/` | `lib/features/iam-profile/` | `components2/iam-profile/` |

When unsure: **routes stay thin, features own truth, components own paint.**
